{"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DatagramBasedProtocol"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Send one or more data messages from "},{"code":"datagramBased","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" in one go."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"send","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"messages","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp","text":"UnsafeMutablePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"text":"GOutputMessage","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":">!, "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"numMessages"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"flags"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"text":"timeout","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"gint64","preciseIdentifier":"c:glibconfig.h@T@gint64","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"cancellable"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef","text":"CancellableRef","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV"},{"text":"? = nil) ","kind":"text"},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"messages"},{"type":"text","text":" must point to an array of "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/OutputMessage"},{"text":" structs and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"numMessages","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" must be the length of this array. Each ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/OutputMessage","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"contains an address to send the data to, and a pointer to an array of","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/OutputVector","isActive":true},{"text":" structs to describe the buffers that the data to be sent","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"for each message will be gathered from.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"flags","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" modify how the message is sent. The commonly available arguments","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"for this are available in the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketMsgFlags","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" enum, but the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"values there are the same as the system values, and the flags","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"are passed in as-is, so you can pass in system-specific flags too.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The other members of ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/OutputMessage","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" are treated as described in its"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"documentation.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"timeout"},{"text":" is negative the call will block until ","type":"text"},{"code":"numMessages","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" have been"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"sent, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancellable"},{"type":"text","text":" is cancelled, or an error occurs."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"code":"timeout","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is 0 the call will send up to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"numMessages"},{"type":"text","text":" without blocking,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"or will return "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"wouldBlock"},{"type":"text","text":" if there is no space to send messages."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"code":"timeout","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is positive the call will block on the same conditions as if","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"timeout"},{"type":"text","text":" were negative. If the timeout is reached before any messages are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"sent, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"timedOut"},{"type":"text","text":" is returned, otherwise it will return the number"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of messages sent before timing out."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To be notified when messages can be sent, wait for the [out](\/\/documentation\/gobject\/out condition."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Note though that you may still receive ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"wouldBlock"},{"text":" from","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_datagram_based_send_messages()"},{"type":"text","text":" even if you were previously notified of a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[out](\/\/documentation\/gobject\/out condition. (On Windows in particular, this is very common due to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the way the underlying APIs work.)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If the connection is shut down or closed (by calling ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_socket_close()"},{"type":"text","text":" or"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_socket_shutdown()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" with "},{"code":"shutdown_write","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" set, if it’s a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"example), all calls to this function will return "},{"code":"closed","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"On error -1 is returned and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"error"},{"text":" is set accordingly. An error will only","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"be returned if zero messages could be sent; otherwise the number of messages","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"successfully sent before the error will be returned. If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancellable"},{"text":" is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"cancelled, ","type":"text"},{"code":"cancelled","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is returned as with any other error."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/datagrambasedprotocol\/send(messages:nummessages:flags:timeout:cancellable:)-5yayj"]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DatagramBasedProtocol\/send(messages:numMessages:flags:timeout:cancellable:)-5yayj","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"extendedModule":"GIO","role":"symbol","externalID":"s:3GIO21DatagramBasedProtocolPAAE4send8messages11numMessages5flags7timeout11cancellableSiSpySo15_GOutputMessageVGSg_S2is5Int64VAA14CancellableRefVSgtKF","title":"send(messages:numMessages:flags:timeout:cancellable:)","roleHeading":"Instance Method","symbolKind":"method","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"send"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"messages"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp","text":"UnsafeMutablePointer"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"GOutputMessage","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":">!, "},{"text":"numMessages","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"flags","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"text":"timeout","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:glibconfig.h@T@gint64","text":"gint64"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"cancellable"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","text":"CancellableRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"?) "},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"}]},"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/SocketMsgFlags":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketMsgFlags","abstract":[{"text":"Flags used in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_socket_receive_message()"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_socket_send_message()"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The flags listed in the enum are some commonly available flags, but the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"values used for them are the same as on the platform, and any other flags"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"are passed in\/out as is. So to use a platform specific flag, just include","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the right system header and pass in the flag."}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"SocketMsgFlags"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/socketmsgflags","title":"SocketMsgFlags","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SocketMsgFlags","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/DatagramBasedProtocol":{"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/datagrambasedprotocol","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Interface for socket-like objects with datagram semantics.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DatagramBasedProtocol","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"DatagramBasedProtocol"}],"title":"DatagramBasedProtocol","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"DatagramBasedProtocol"}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO":{"type":"topic","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","title":"GIO","url":"\/documentation\/gio","role":"collection","kind":"symbol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/OutputMessage":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Structure used for scatter\/gather data output when sending multiple"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"messages or packets in one go. You generally pass in an array of","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"GOutputVectors","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and the operation will use all the buffers as if they"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"were one buffer."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/outputmessage","type":"topic","title":"OutputMessage","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OutputMessage","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"OutputMessage"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/OutputMessage"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/DatagramBasedProtocol/send(messages:numMessage